	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p><addressee>Revd I Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Dear Sir&#44; I have you<lb/> annexed&#44; statement of collections<lb/> made on a&#47;c Occident&#44; as well as<lb/> sales of Book&#39;s since last report<lb/> together amounting to Fifty 35&#47;00. Dols<lb/> for which I hand you enclosed<lb/> my check on Mechanics Bank<lb/> <placeName>New York</placeName> less Exchange 25c for Fifty<lb/> 10&#47;00 Dolls.  I am pleased to learn<lb/> of the great progress you have made<lb/> in the Bibles completion.  I have<lb/> no doubt it will prove the means<lb/> of amply repaying you for all your<lb/> labors bestowed in the publishing<lb/> way.  Many Christians are anxious<lb/> to see the work&#44; &#38; I have no a number<lb/> will be sold to them.</p>
				<p>We have had two discourses<lb/> delivered in our Synagogue by<lb/> our <persName>Rev Mr. Jacobs</persName> in behalf of <del>our</del><lb/> suffering humanly in <placeName>New Orleans</placeName><lb/> <persName>Mr. Jacobs</persName> was the first Minis<lb/>ter in our city who suggested</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p>&#38; carried out this mode<lb/> of enlisting the feelings of our<lb/> citizens towards the pecuniary<lb/> aid of the people of our<lb/> sister city <add>&#63;</add> but<lb/> a very short notice was given<lb/> through the papers&#44; but omitted<lb/> to be announced on <date>Sabbath</date><lb/> <sic>preceeding</sic> the discourse&#44; which<lb/> was to be on <date>Sunday</date>&#44; &#38; which<lb/> omission &#38; short notice com<lb/>bined prevented a great<lb/> number from attending<lb/> we secured one Hundred<lb/> Dolls &#38; remitted it to the <add>&#63;</add><lb/> society.  Since then we have been<lb/> solicited by the Benevolent Society<lb/> of <add>&#63;</add> &#38; we have from the 2d<lb/> <add>&#63;</add> more to remit.  So you<lb/> must admit that our <add>&#63;</add><lb/> Hazan &#38; Sec<add>&#63;</add> has done some<lb/> good by his example &#38; precepts<lb/> Little or but a small amt has as<lb/> yet been collected from other <add>&#63;</add><lb/> I wish you would notice them<lb/> <add>&#63;</add> above sealed in your next<lb/> Occident for altho our congregation<lb/> after the <add>&#63;</add> and dispersed circu<lb/>lary for aid to the several <placeName>North</placeName> &#38; <placeName>South</placeName><lb/> the only response we ever got was your Ocd<lb/> <add>&#63;</add> candlesticks which I suppose your trustees<lb/> then&#44; intended we should con<add>&#63;</add> them<lb/> into gold.</p>
			<pb n="3"/>
				<p>so it is.  I promise myself the<lb/> pleasure of soon seeing you<lb/> perhaps spending the 2<lb/> days of yon <add>&#63;</add> in your city<lb/> I wonder if <persName>Mrs Himman</persName><lb/> will have room to accom<lb/>modate one&#63; do you know<lb/> our city  remains<add>&#63;</add> usually<lb/> healthy&#44; will produce<lb/> an early business which<lb/> compels me to leave home<lb/> earlier than is my usual<lb/> habit.  I expect to be in<lb/> your city on <date><sic>friday</sic></date> after<lb/> eve of <date><sic>Roshanna</sic></date></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Hoping this will meet<lb/> you in health if not<lb/> in wealth</p>
			<p rend="indent(8)">I am as always</p>
			<p rend="indent(7)">your friend</p>
			<p rend="indent(7)"><persName role="author">Samuel Hart Sen</persName></p>
